1
00:00:02,434 --> 00:00:04,231
Man: Scotland
didn't invent football,

2
00:00:04,336 --> 00:00:06,065
but we'll take
a back seat to no one

3
00:00:06,171 --> 00:00:07,729
in our passion
for the game.

4
00:00:07,840 --> 00:00:11,207
With 40 professional teams
in a country of five million,

5
00:00:11,310 --> 00:00:13,642
football is as much a part
of the national fabric

6
00:00:13,746 --> 00:00:15,907
as single malt
and bad weather.

7
00:00:16,014 --> 00:00:17,504
Some say it's a religion.

8
00:00:17,616 --> 00:00:20,744
If so, there are two denominations
in this church--

9
00:00:20,853 --> 00:00:22,753
Celtic and Rangers.

10
00:00:22,855 --> 00:00:25,085
One Catholic,
one Protestant--

11
00:00:25,190 --> 00:00:26,748
us and them.

12
00:00:26,859 --> 00:00:28,918
The forces of evil
and darkness

13
00:00:29,027 --> 00:00:31,587
known collectively
as ''The Old Firm.''

14
00:00:31,697 --> 00:00:33,255
There maybe no rivalry

15
00:00:33,365 --> 00:00:35,265
in all of football
to match theirs,

16
00:00:35,367 --> 00:00:37,699
maybe not in all
of sports.

17
00:00:37,803 --> 00:00:40,738
For over a century, the players
have bashed heads on the field,

18
00:00:40,839 --> 00:00:42,534
their supporters off it.

19
00:00:42,641 --> 00:00:44,370
Together,
they've dominated the game

20
00:00:44,476 --> 00:00:46,103
and won
the Scottish Cup more

21
00:00:46,211 --> 00:00:48,771
than all the other teams
put together.

22
00:00:48,881 --> 00:00:51,577
But this is not a story
about Celtic and Rangers.

23
00:00:51,683 --> 00:00:54,447
There's not enough lager
in all the pubs in Glasgow

24
00:00:54,553 --> 00:00:56,817
to do it justice
in a single sitting.

25
00:00:56,922 --> 00:01:00,016
Besides, only a fool
would try to get it right.

26
00:01:00,125 --> 00:01:02,389
But any story about football
in this land

27
00:01:02,494 --> 00:01:04,223
is colored by their rivalry.

28
00:01:04,329 --> 00:01:06,729
Whatever your team,
big or small,

29
00:01:06,832 --> 00:01:09,699
football in Scotland isn't
a matter of life or death--

30
00:01:09,802 --> 00:01:11,736
it's more important.

31
00:01:15,774 --> 00:01:19,210
( bagpipe music plays )

32
00:01:43,535 --> 00:01:46,766
Minister: Dear Lord,
our Father and our Savior...

33
00:01:46,872 --> 00:01:50,672
please welcome one of our own
to Your flock.

34
00:01:52,177 --> 00:01:55,476
Alex Wilson
loved Kilnockie football

35
00:01:55,581 --> 00:01:58,846
almost as much as he loved
his wife, Annie,

36
00:01:58,951 --> 00:02:01,385
and his three sons.

37
00:02:01,487 --> 00:02:05,719
For 47 years, he never missed
a home match.

38
00:02:05,824 --> 00:02:08,850
So it is fitting
that we send him off today

39
00:02:08,961 --> 00:02:12,055
in the place he liked
to call home.

40
00:02:13,532 --> 00:02:16,194
A family man,
and a football man,

41
00:02:16,301 --> 00:02:18,599
Alex Wilson
played the game of life

42
00:02:18,704 --> 00:02:20,899
with loyalty
to those he loved,

43
00:02:21,006 --> 00:02:24,032
with kindness to all he met.

44
00:02:24,142 --> 00:02:27,407
He was a generous man
who never stopped trying

45
00:02:27,513 --> 00:02:30,744
to help others--
right up to the final whistle.

46
00:02:33,619 --> 00:02:37,578
May you rest in peace,
Alexander Wilson,

47
00:02:37,689 --> 00:02:40,590
and may you always run
with the lads.

48
00:02:41,860 --> 00:02:44,795
He's a fucking headcase,
Peter, a waster, eh?

49
00:02:44,897 --> 00:02:47,161
What are you trying
to build,

50
00:02:47,266 --> 00:02:49,598
a football team
or a distillery?

51
00:02:49,701 --> 00:02:52,602
- He scores goals.
- Oh, aye, he could.

52
00:02:52,704 --> 00:02:55,264
Couldn't score
in a brothel now.

53
00:02:55,374 --> 00:02:57,535
Why do you think
he was available?

54
00:03:00,212 --> 00:03:02,578
You know, Gordon,
I know this is a family affair.

55
00:03:02,681 --> 00:03:05,548
I respect that.
It's none of my business, by the way,

56
00:03:05,651 --> 00:03:07,551
but I want to make sure

57
00:03:07,653 --> 00:03:09,553
you don't put
your personal feelings ahead

58
00:03:09,655 --> 00:03:11,282
of whatever's good
for the team.

59
00:03:11,390 --> 00:03:14,291
Buying a team is different
than running a team.

60
00:03:14,393 --> 00:03:16,156
How do you think the lads
are gonna feel

61
00:03:16,261 --> 00:03:17,922
bringing in a player
who makes more

62
00:03:18,030 --> 00:03:20,055
- than all of them combined?
- You know what?

63
00:03:20,165 --> 00:03:22,725
If they really wanna win,
it's not an issue.

64
00:03:22,834 --> 00:03:24,859
- Oh.
- He puts fans in the stands.

65
00:03:24,970 --> 00:03:26,562
You know why?
Simple.

66
00:03:26,672 --> 00:03:28,196
He's really good.

67
00:03:28,307 --> 00:03:30,036
He can score,
he plays defense,

68
00:03:30,142 --> 00:03:31,609
he anticipates,
he can see the field.

69
00:03:31,710 --> 00:03:32,972
He's won two Golden Boots.

70
00:03:33,078 --> 00:03:35,410
This guy's gonna give us
the punch we need, Gordon,

71
00:03:35,514 --> 00:03:38,415
to make a run at the Cup.
Don't you wanna win a Cup?

72
00:03:38,517 --> 00:03:40,644
We've won the first
three matches without him.

73
00:03:40,752 --> 00:03:43,380
I know, but now
the big boys are here.

74
00:03:43,488 --> 00:03:45,012
Teams win the Cup, Peter,

75
00:03:45,123 --> 00:03:48,115
not prima donnas reminiscing
over their past glories.

76
00:03:49,661 --> 00:03:51,458
I used to have hair...

77
00:03:51,563 --> 00:03:53,258
once upon a time.

78
00:03:53,365 --> 00:03:54,423
Eh?

79
00:04:23,061 --> 00:04:24,824
( screeching )

80
00:04:26,298 --> 00:04:27,890
Bloody menace !

81
00:04:30,035 --> 00:04:32,560
Where the hell
do you think you are?

82
00:04:32,671 --> 00:04:34,832
Fucking nutter.

83
00:04:36,875 --> 00:04:39,070
Peter: There's never
a League Champion year.

84
00:04:39,177 --> 00:04:41,702
Not even a semifinal
appearance in a Cup.

85
00:04:41,813 --> 00:04:44,748
Nothing.
1899 to 1999, nothing.

86
00:04:46,685 --> 00:04:48,550
- The wilderness years.
- Gordon: Yeah.

87
00:04:48,654 --> 00:04:51,452
Peter, is the meeting over?

88
00:04:59,631 --> 00:05:01,189
No.

89
00:05:03,301 --> 00:05:07,032
Gordon, I'm thinking about
moving this team to Dublin.

90
00:05:07,139 --> 00:05:10,108
A Scottish football team
in Ireland?

91
00:05:10,208 --> 00:05:12,836
Next you'll be wanting us
to play Gaelic football

92
00:05:12,944 --> 00:05:14,377
and use our fucking hands.

93
00:05:14,479 --> 00:05:16,970
You should be locked up.
You're kidding.

94
00:05:17,082 --> 00:05:19,880
They're so hungry
for professional football.

95
00:05:19,985 --> 00:05:20,917
Really hungry.

96
00:05:21,019 --> 00:05:22,509
And they've got
a brand new stadium.

97
00:05:22,621 --> 00:05:24,145
Don't you want more
than this?

98
00:05:24,256 --> 00:05:25,382
I do.

99
00:05:25,490 --> 00:05:26,684
After a hundred years,

100
00:05:26,792 --> 00:05:30,023
you want to move
the Kilnockie team to Ireland?

101
00:05:31,263 --> 00:05:34,289
You're talking about
the heartbeat of this town.

102
00:05:34,399 --> 00:05:36,924
10 decades of tradition.

103
00:05:37,035 --> 00:05:39,503
I mean, you're talking about--

104
00:05:39,604 --> 00:05:41,663
you're talking about my job.

105
00:05:41,773 --> 00:05:43,900
You're not going anywhere.

106
00:05:45,544 --> 00:05:47,068
I'll tell you another thing,

107
00:05:47,179 --> 00:05:49,409
Jackie McQuillan's
gonna make a difference too.

108
00:05:55,454 --> 00:05:58,355
I want to be there
when you tell 'em

109
00:05:58,457 --> 00:06:00,357
you're moving the team
to Ireland.

110
00:06:00,459 --> 00:06:02,188
Minister:
Earth to earth,

111
00:06:02,294 --> 00:06:04,455
ashes to ashes,
dust to dust,

112
00:06:04,563 --> 00:06:06,997
in the sure
and certain hope

113
00:06:07,099 --> 00:06:09,329
of resurrection
to eternal life,

114
00:06:09,434 --> 00:06:12,426
through our Lord
Jesus Christ

115
00:06:12,537 --> 00:06:14,095
Amen.

116
00:06:15,474 --> 00:06:16,907
Boylie.

117
00:06:17,008 --> 00:06:19,499
Come on, son, pass back!

118
00:06:19,611 --> 00:06:21,272
Go on, Boylie, bury it.

119
00:06:21,379 --> 00:06:23,210
Well done.
Good save, Brian.

120
00:06:23,315 --> 00:06:25,647
Go on, Kirky.

121
00:06:25,751 --> 00:06:28,481
Yes, good save.

122
00:06:31,690 --> 00:06:33,715
Get in there, Silky.

123
00:06:33,825 --> 00:06:35,656
Come on, Silky.

124
00:06:39,698 --> 00:06:42,462
Jesus Andy, you can't score
if the ball's not in the net.

125
00:06:42,567 --> 00:06:44,762
Look, lads,
it's where you put it,

126
00:06:44,870 --> 00:06:46,531
not where you point it
that counts.

127
00:06:46,638 --> 00:06:49,607
Aye, goes for your women
as well, right?

128
00:06:49,708 --> 00:06:52,074
Okay, Romeo,
you show 'em how it's done.

129
00:06:57,215 --> 00:06:59,274
( speaking foreign language )

130
00:06:59,384 --> 00:07:01,443
There's three points
in American football, cap.

131
00:07:01,553 --> 00:07:03,646
Okay, smart-mouth,
let's see how well you do.

132
00:07:03,755 --> 00:07:06,383
- Let's put the Yank in the net.
- Give 'em hell, Kelsey.

133
00:07:12,597 --> 00:07:14,189
Well done, Kelsey.

134
00:07:14,299 --> 00:07:16,358
Not bad for a pizza boy
from the States.

135
00:07:18,370 --> 00:07:20,702
Well done, Kelsey.

136
00:07:20,806 --> 00:07:22,205
Go on, go on.

137
00:07:22,307 --> 00:07:23,365
Where, where's he going?

138
00:07:23,475 --> 00:07:25,443
Hey!
Where's he going?

139
00:07:25,544 --> 00:07:27,034
Hey, Diego! Hey!

140
00:07:27,145 --> 00:07:29,238
- Where's he going?
- Home?

141
00:07:29,347 --> 00:07:31,042
I don't think he likes
the weather.

142
00:07:31,149 --> 00:07:32,616
Hey, come here.

143
00:07:34,286 --> 00:07:36,447
Diego, come here.

144
00:07:36,555 --> 00:07:38,386
Come back here !

145
00:07:38,490 --> 00:07:40,219
Hey!

146
00:07:44,362 --> 00:07:47,456
Training begins at 10:00 sharp.

147
00:07:47,566 --> 00:07:49,124
You better
tell the sheeps, Gordon.

148
00:07:49,234 --> 00:07:52,465
They seem to like the roads better
than they like the fields.

149
00:07:52,571 --> 00:07:54,163
I didn't want this.

150
00:07:54,272 --> 00:07:55,739
Nor did I.

151
00:07:55,841 --> 00:07:58,207
But I'm here to play football.

152
00:07:58,310 --> 00:08:00,471
You were always a fuck-up,
McQuillan.

153
00:08:00,579 --> 00:08:02,604
Always will be.

154
00:08:04,382 --> 00:08:06,509
Nice to see you too,
Gordon.

155
00:08:06,618 --> 00:08:07,846
Aye.

156
00:08:20,599 --> 00:08:22,533
Fucking hell.

157
00:08:24,202 --> 00:08:25,464
Alan Barnes, Jackie.

158
00:08:25,570 --> 00:08:27,868
- Pleasure to meet you.
- How are you doing, Alan?

159
00:08:27,973 --> 00:08:30,771
We're probably happier to have you
than you are to be here,

160
00:08:30,876 --> 00:08:32,844
but you know, just--

161
00:08:32,944 --> 00:08:34,878
just think of it as Parkhead.

162
00:08:34,980 --> 00:08:37,448
A wee bit different.
What do you think?

163
00:08:38,817 --> 00:08:40,876
- Okay then.
- I'll show you the guys.

164
00:08:48,493 --> 00:08:50,154
Woman:
I wonder how it went today--

165
00:08:50,262 --> 00:08:51,991
Jackie and Dad together again.

166
00:08:52,097 --> 00:08:54,122
If Jackie showed up.

167
00:08:54,232 --> 00:08:57,690
Yeah, well, he told me
he was going to.

168
00:08:57,802 --> 00:09:00,635
He told you a lot of things
he was going to do.

169
00:09:01,740 --> 00:09:04,106
We've started
seeing each other again.

170
00:09:05,944 --> 00:09:08,344
Landing in the Second Division
hit him hard, Mom.

171
00:09:09,614 --> 00:09:12,378
- Let alone here.
- He's lucky to be here.

172
00:09:12,484 --> 00:09:15,920
He's brought enough pain
to your life, Kate.

173
00:09:16,021 --> 00:09:18,148
He's little Jackie's father.

174
00:09:18,256 --> 00:09:21,020
You can't undo
what's been done.

175
00:09:23,461 --> 00:09:26,521
Loving them is never
the problem, is it, Mom?

176
00:09:26,631 --> 00:09:28,360
It's everything else,

177
00:09:28,466 --> 00:09:30,866
when you share your husband
with this game.

178
00:09:30,969 --> 00:09:33,460
Your father and I have been
married for 40 years.

179
00:09:33,571 --> 00:09:35,539
It's not the amount
of time, Mom.

180
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:38,632
When you marry a football man,
you become a football wife.

181
00:09:38,743 --> 00:09:41,041
Talent, temperament--

182
00:09:41,146 --> 00:09:42,545
the church they believe in.

183
00:09:42,647 --> 00:09:44,842
Inside, I swear to God,

184
00:09:44,950 --> 00:09:48,545
they are all driven,
stubborn, selfish,

185
00:09:49,854 --> 00:09:52,220
and as competitive as a pack
of street dogs.

186
00:09:52,324 --> 00:09:55,384
And those are probably just
the best traits.

187
00:09:55,493 --> 00:09:57,290
The truth is that...

188
00:09:57,395 --> 00:10:01,263
Jackie and Dad are actually more
alike than they are different.

189
00:10:01,366 --> 00:10:02,424
( door opens )

190
00:10:06,338 --> 00:10:07,600
Hi, Dad.

191
00:11:02,694 --> 00:11:05,219
Hi, I'm Andy Gray.
Welcome to ''Sky Sports,''

192
00:11:05,330 --> 00:11:07,025
here to talk about
the headline

193
00:11:07,132 --> 00:11:09,566
that's dominated
Scottish football.

194
00:11:09,667 --> 00:11:11,567
It is, of course,
the recent signing

195
00:11:11,669 --> 00:11:13,398
by Kilnockie
of Jackie McQuillan,

196
00:11:13,505 --> 00:11:15,405
twice a Golden Boot winner.

197
00:11:15,507 --> 00:11:17,737
No doubt the supporters
will be looking forward

198
00:11:17,842 --> 00:11:19,901
to some great
goal scoring magic.

199
00:11:20,011 --> 00:11:21,911
So, let's take a look back
at the career

200
00:11:22,013 --> 00:11:23,844
of this legendary
Celtic striker.

201
00:11:50,742 --> 00:11:52,266
Jackie !

202
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:16,732
Gray:
The question now is...

203
00:12:16,835 --> 00:12:19,736
he may be down,
but is he out?

204
00:12:19,838 --> 00:12:21,237
Will the gamble pay off

205
00:12:21,339 --> 00:12:23,239
for Kilnockie's
American owner,

206
00:12:23,341 --> 00:12:26,572
Peter Cameron,
and manager, Gordon McCleod?

207
00:12:32,851 --> 00:12:34,751
All of Scotland
will be watching.

208
00:12:54,639 --> 00:12:56,539
Hey, Jackie.

209
00:12:56,641 --> 00:12:58,370
How are you doing?

210
00:12:58,476 --> 00:13:00,410
I just wanted to say
what an honor it was

211
00:13:00,512 --> 00:13:03,072
to be playing on
the same field with you today.

212
00:13:03,181 --> 00:13:05,547
When I was in college
I used to watch

213
00:13:05,650 --> 00:13:07,550
the satellite feed
of your matches.

214
00:13:07,652 --> 00:13:09,279
And I remember the time

215
00:13:09,387 --> 00:13:12,550
where you beat
three Rangers defenders,

216
00:13:12,657 --> 00:13:14,386
and dinked the ball

217
00:13:14,492 --> 00:13:16,722
over the keeper's head
to get the winner--

218
00:13:16,828 --> 00:13:18,386
in injury time.

219
00:13:20,331 --> 00:13:22,561
Man, that was--

220
00:13:22,667 --> 00:13:24,066
that was some goal.

221
00:13:27,172 --> 00:13:29,299
I'm sorry,
I forgot your name.

222
00:13:31,009 --> 00:13:32,408
Kelsey.

223
00:13:33,711 --> 00:13:35,906
Kelsey, let me give you
a piece of advice.

224
00:13:37,682 --> 00:13:39,582
You don't live
in the past, son.

225
00:13:42,687 --> 00:13:45,247
- Announcer: St. Mirren...
- Man: Shh.

226
00:13:45,356 --> 00:13:47,586
Announcer:
...will play Kilmarnock.

227
00:13:53,298 --> 00:13:56,358
Dundee will play

228
00:13:56,467 --> 00:13:58,196
Queen of the South.

229
00:14:03,041 --> 00:14:04,565
Kilnockie...

230
00:14:06,344 --> 00:14:08,073
will play Dumbarton.

231
00:14:08,179 --> 00:14:09,703
( cheering )

232
00:14:22,827 --> 00:14:24,556
( phone rings )

233
00:14:24,662 --> 00:14:26,220
- Hello?
- Hello, Irene.

234
00:14:26,331 --> 00:14:28,231
- Is Gordon there?
- Uh-huh, Ian, he is.

235
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:32,060
- Great news.
- He's just coming.

236
00:14:35,506 --> 00:14:36,905
- Ian.
- Hey, gaffer.

237
00:14:37,008 --> 00:14:38,737
- Aye.
- Have you heard the draw?

238
00:14:38,843 --> 00:14:40,003
Dumbarton, at home.

239
00:14:40,111 --> 00:14:42,136
Gives us a right chance
to get through, eh?

240
00:14:42,247 --> 00:14:44,078
Only if we score
more goals than they do.

241
00:14:44,182 --> 00:14:47,083
- Oh, I'm sure we will.
- Aye, it's great.

242
00:14:47,185 --> 00:14:49,653
- Okay then, bye.
- Talk to you later.

243
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:04,700
Dumbarton, eh?

244
00:15:06,804 --> 00:15:08,704
Maybe we'll go one more.

245
00:15:08,806 --> 00:15:10,364
Oh, aye, maybe.

246
00:15:15,647 --> 00:15:18,548
Was Jackie
at training today?

247
00:15:18,650 --> 00:15:20,117
Jackie?

248
00:15:21,319 --> 00:15:23,048
Late.

249
00:15:26,824 --> 00:15:28,382
Sheep on the road.

250
00:15:30,995 --> 00:15:33,054
If it's not one thing
it's another.

251
00:15:33,164 --> 00:15:34,722
Mmm.

252
00:15:40,672 --> 00:15:43,232
I thought he was out
of my life forever.

253
00:15:57,955 --> 00:16:01,686
Are we planning on having
another child, Gordon?

254
00:16:01,793 --> 00:16:03,693
Eh?

255
00:16:05,897 --> 00:16:07,524
( scoffs )

256
00:16:10,468 --> 00:16:13,699
Then you might try saying hello
to the one you do have.

257
00:16:15,139 --> 00:16:16,697
The only one.

258
00:16:37,729 --> 00:16:39,390
